{"title":"End-to-End Urban Driving by Imitating a Reinforcement Learning Coach","domain":"ROBOTICS","seeds":[{"problem":"Rule-based automated experts in simulators (e.g., CARLA Autopilot) are suboptimal coaches for end-to-end driving and model-free RL for urban driving often suffers from poor sample efficiency and unstable training.","method":"Roach: a PPO-based RL expert that maps bird’s-eye-view (BEV) semantics plus ego measurements to continuous low-level actions parameterized by Beta distributions (bounded support) instead of Gaussians, improving optimization and avoiding squashing/clipping. It introduces an exploration loss that, in the final steps before specific terminal infractions (collision, red light/sign, route deviation, blockage), shifts the policy toward event-specific action priors (e.g., decelerate to avoid collisions/lights, accelerate to escape blockage, uniform steering near route deviation) via KL to prior Beta distributions. Trained from scratch without expert data, Roach achieves stable, sample-efficient learning (~10M steps across Town1–6) and sets a new performance upper bound on CARLA, yielding higher driving scores than the Autopilot by better handling traffic lights."},{"problem":"End-to-end imitation learners trained with hard, deterministic actions from automated experts generalize poorly under covariate shift and miss informative supervision signals beyond actions.","method":"Use the RL coach as a teacher to provide dense, on-policy, informative targets for IL. Replace the L1 action loss with a KL-divergence to the coach’s action distribution (Beta) as soft targets; add a value head to the IL model trained to regress the coach’s state-value; and match the coach’s latent feature (BEV-based j_RL) via an MSE feature loss. Implemented on a DA-RB/CILRS agent with monocular input (and command-conditioned branch or command-as-input variant), these supervisions significantly improve generalization, achieving ~78% success rate in the NoCrash-dense new town & new weather setting and state-of-the-art/expert-level performance on CARLA public LeaderBoard routes; feature and value supervisions show synergy, with best gains when command information is included to support feature matching."}]}
